HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 110
By Keisling
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Allie Bailey on her
receipt of the Governor's Volunteer Stars Award.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those estimable citizens who have dedicated their time and energies to helping
others; and
WHEREAS, each year, 1.3 million Tennessee volunteers give over 99 million hours of
community service, contributing $2.6 billion to Tennessee's economy; and
WHEREAS, these volunteers are the backbone of our communities, and by donating
their time and talents to fulfill needs that would otherwise go unmet, they embody the spirit of
giving; and
WHEREAS, Allie Bailey of Scott County is one such exemplary person, who is a
recipient of the Governor's Volunteer Stars Award in recognition of her laudable commitment to
her community; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Bailey began serving her community as a high school sophomore,
volunteering for Schools Together Allowing No Drugs (STAND), and she served as vice
president of the youth coalition; and
WHEREAS, during college, Allie Bailey returned to Scott County to volunteer with
STAND, the local homeless shelter, the women's shelter, and other nonprofit organizations; her
efforts have touched countless lives, bringing hope to those in need; and
WHEREAS, a dedicated volunteer, Ms. Bailey chose to continue her work full time with
STAND after graduating from the University of Tennessee, Chattanooga; her journey from a
youth volunteer to a dedicated professional showcases how service and determination can truly
transform a community; and
